# Week 2 — OT Network Setup & PLC Deployment

## Overview

Week 2 focuses on building the **Operational Technology (OT) layer** of the ICS-RedSim lab.
This phase involves deploying a virtual **Programmable Logic Controller (PLC)** and preparing the base industrial network used for communication between control systems.

The PLC is implemented using **OpenPLC**, which simulates real industrial controllers used in manufacturing and critical infrastructure environments.

The OT environment forms the core of the simulated industrial plant that will later be monitored by SCADA and security tools.

---

# Objectives

The primary goals of Week 2 include:

* Create the OT network environment
* Deploy a virtual PLC system
* Install and configure OpenPLC
* Implement basic PLC control logic
* Enable Modbus TCP communication
* Verify PLC functionality

---

# OT Network Environment

The Operational Technology zone contains the industrial devices responsible for controlling the simulated process.

### OT Zone Components

| Component     | Role                                  |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| PLC VM        | Industrial controller running OpenPLC |
| Ubuntu Server | Operating system for PLC runtime      |
| Modbus TCP    | Industrial communication protocol     |

This setup allows the PLC to communicate with SCADA systems and monitoring tools in later phases.

---

# Virtual Machine Setup

A dedicated virtual machine was created to host the PLC runtime.

| Parameter        | Configuration                |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------- |
| VM Name          | PLC_VM                       |
| Operating System | Ubuntu Server 22.04          |
| CPU              | 2 Cores                      |
| RAM              | 2 GB                         |
| Disk             | 20 GB                        |
| Network          | OT Network (192.168.1.0/24) |

The PLC VM is placed inside the **OT network segment** to mimic industrial device isolation.

---

# PLC Deployment

The PLC functionality is implemented using **OpenPLC**, which provides an open-source platform for simulating industrial control systems.

Key capabilities of OpenPLC include:

* Ladder Logic programming
* Modbus TCP communication
* Real-time process control
* Integration with SCADA systems

OpenPLC allows development of PLC logic similar to real industrial controllers.

---

# PLC Control Logic

A basic control logic was implemented to simulate a simple industrial process.

### Process Variables

| Variable   | Function                         |
| ---------- | -------------------------------- |
| Pump       | Controls water pump operation    |
| Tank Level | Represents simulated tank sensor |
| Alarm      | Indicates high-level condition   |

---

# Modbus Communication

Communication between the PLC and other industrial components uses **Modbus TCP**, one of the most common protocols in industrial automation.

### Modbus Register Mapping

| Register Type    | Address | Function         |
| ---------------- | ------- | ---------------- |
| Coil             | 1       | Pump control     |
| Holding Register | 0       | Tank level value |
| Coil             | 3       | Alarm indicator  |

This register mapping allows SCADA systems to read and write control values.

